{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_81","type":"agent_message","text":"The runtime behavior finally makes sense. The earlier `reference.conf` entries were conditional, so the config resources were registered in the image but still invisible at startup, before any `akka.event.slf4j.*` type had been reached. Once I forced unconditional resource registration, startup moved past config loading and exposed the next real gap: Akka reflectively loads logging classes from config strings, and those classes are missing reflection metadata. I’m moving the fix to where it belongs: unconditional config resources plus reflective constructor entries on the Akka actor side."}}
